# Content Structure

## Blog Posts (MDX)

| Location | Description |
|---|---|
| `content/blog/{slug}.mdx` | Published posts |
| `content/blog/drafts/{slug}.mdx` | Draft posts (`draft: true`) |
| `content/blog/quizzes/{slug}-quiz.json` | Companion quiz for each post |

### Required Frontmatter

```yaml
---
title: "Post Title"          # Always use double quotes (apostrophes break single quotes)
slug: post-slug
excerpt: >-
  150-160 char SEO description.
publishedAt: 'YYYY-MM-DD'
tags:
  - tag1
  - tag2
author: Sandeep Reddy Alalla
featured: true
course:
  id: course-id
  module: module-name
  order: 1
draft: false                  # true for drafts
---
```

### Post Structure

1. Personal narrative hook (specific problem, first person)
2. What the post covers + intended audience + prerequisites
3. Table of contents with anchor links
4. Main content sections (progressive disclosure: simple → complex)
5. Key Takeaways (numbered list)
6. `<Quiz quizId="{slug}" />` component
7. "Happy coding!"

## Courses

Each course has `content/courses/{course-id}/meta.json` with:
- `id`, `title`, `description`, `modules[]` (each with `id`, `name`, `description`, `order`), `author`

Blog posts link to courses via `course.id` and `course.module` in frontmatter.

Current courses: `javascript`, `html-css`, `low-level-design`

## Challenges

`content/challenges/{slug}.json` with: `slug`, `title`, `description`, `difficulty`, `concepts[]`, `featured`, `blogPostSlug`, `tags[]`

Reference implementations live in `scripts/{slug}.js` with integrated test runners.

## Quizzes

`content/blog/quizzes/{slug}-quiz.json` with 6-10 questions.
Types: `multiple-choice`, `multiple-select`, `true-false`.
Each question has `explanation` that teaches, not just confirms.
